<TEXT>
mayor ed gray is tired of his town 
being made a laughingstock over ufo sightings he considers a hoax 
but some merchants are cashing in on the controversy 
tourism is looking up thanks to a series of reported ufo 
spottings since 1988 merchants are churning out ufo books jewelry 
and tshirts picturing a beachgoing alien catching some rays 
from a flying saucer 
gray isnt laughing 
i have a real moral problem with my city being couched as a 
ufo phenomenon when its not he said in a recent interview 
gulf breeze in the florida panhandle made tabloid history in 
1988 when ed walters a local builder reported the first sightings 
and produced photographs he claimed were of ufos 
he also told of being lifted off the ground by a beam of blue 
light from a flying saucer and getting a visit from 
spanishspeaking extraterrestrials who talked about bananas he and 
his wife frances even wrote a book about it called the gulf 
breeze sightings 
interest in the towns own brand of upward mobility waned until 
recently 
first the mutual ufo network a ufo research organization held 
its annual symposium in neighboring pensacola from july 68 the 
threeday event attracted 600 people 
then six us soldiers were arrested july 13 in the gulf breeze 
area after slipping away from their army intelligence unit in west 
germany a friend of one of the soldiers who were discharged last 
week for desertion said they went to gulf breeze because they 
believed the end of the world was near and jesus would return in a 
spaceship 
the two events generated plenty of publicity the miami herald 
labeled gulf breeze americas flying saucer spaceport crews 
from the television programs unsolved mysteries a current 
affair and inside edition were here last week to do ufo shows 
gray agreed to be interviewed on each show 
the general feedback is its time somebody told it like it is 
and defended the city said gray who is a banker 
some business owners think the ufo flap is good for the beach 
town of 6200 because it has brought untold free publicity and 
attracted tourists 
sheilah bowman director of tourism and convention development 
for the pensacola area chamber of commerce said ufo tour groups 
are being arranged 
gulf breeze travel agent linda belcher who handled 600 plane 
tickets for the ufo symposium also said the publicity has been 
beneficial 
it brought in a lot of money to the gulf breeze merchants when 
they desperately needed it she said 
among souvenirs on sale are 13995 14 caratgold necklaces 
depicting a spaceship 4895 spaceship watches and tshirts 
depicting a flying saucer over gulf breeze and the words 
extraterrestrial tourist 
belcher and bowman said they are undecided about the 
authenticity of the sightings but gray said it just doesnt make 
sense for aliens to fly through one of the nations busiest 
military airspaces 
within 40 miles of gulf breeze are two air force bases eglin 
and hurlburt field and two naval air stations pensacola and 
whiting field the aircraft carrier uss lexington is based in 
pensacola and conducts flight training nearby in the gulf of mexico 
gray blames walters for starting the ufo controversy walters 
and his allies say sightings by dozens of other people support his 
claims 
he has used the city for purposes of his rewards gray said 
</TEXT>
