<TEXT>
a passerby became a heroic lifeguard in 
an unlikely locale when a chimpanzee jumped into a 5footdeep moat 
at the detroit zoo 
the man who asked zoo officials not to identify him hauled the 
135pound chimp from the moat sunday and pulled it safely onto an 
island where 10 chimpanzees are kept 
as many as 1000 people were in the area when the 18yearold 
male chimp jumped into the moat zoo spokeswoman pat butkiewicz 
said 
i heard this splash said witness sherry huntington 
people started screaming hes going to drown you saw him 
surface a little bit then go down it was like watching a drowning 
person that poor animal 
in april a 20yearold female chimp drowned in the moat a week 
after the 75million exhibit opened 
