economy alive 
this seems to indicate the consumer is not dead said mark 
m zandi an economist with regional financial associates in west 
chester pa as long as the consumer hangs in there i believe we 
will avoid a recession 
the commerce department said consumer spending totaled a 
seasonally adjusted annual rate of 364 trillion the biggest jump 
since a similar 10 percent gain last january 
