numbers as a result of the commerce departments annual revision 
announced last week the biggest change involved the departments 
579 billion overestimate in wages and salaries which resulted in 
lowering the 1989 savings rate from 54 percent to 46 percent 
americans income after taxes increased 05 percent up from a 
03 percent gain a month earlier wages and salaries rose 130 
billion in june after a 101 billion increase in may 
