ruling united national independence party and church leaders the 
statement said 
reporters were excluded 
since the antigovernment riots in june kaunda a 67yearold 
onetime schoolteacher has announced a referendum next year for 
zambians to decide whether they want a return to a multiparty state 
kaunda who led the british colony of northern rhodesia to 
independence as zambia in 1964 outlawed political opposition 17 
years ago arguing that westernstyle democracy in africa whipped 
up tribal hostilities 
under further pressure for change kaunda also has announced he 
would free all political prisoners release more than 1000 people 
arrested during the riots lifted a dusktodawn curfew and has not 
made any move against a prodemocracy movement forming with former 
