<TEXT>
the soviet union and albania today agreed to 
normalize relations that were broken off 29 years ago during 
moscows split with china the tass news agency reported 
the agreement to reestablish ties and reopen embassies in 
moscow and tirana was reached during talks that were held in 
bulgaria in june and in tirana today tass said 
the soviet delegation was led by deputy foreign minister yuli 
kvitsinsky tass reported 
both sides were guided by a mutual desire to develop the 
relations of friendship and cooperation on the basis of 
sovereignty equality and noninterference in each others internal 
affairs the tass dispatch said 
moscow and tirana pledged to expand contacts in the political 
economic scientific technical and cultural areas it added 
last week soviet foreign ministry spokesman gennady i 
gerasimov had said moscow was seeking to restore diplomatic 
relations with albania europes last bastion of stalinism 
albania broke off diplomatic relations with the soviet union in 
1961 as a result of the kremlins split with china which then 
became albanias chief communist ally 
albania left the warsaw pact in 1968 after the sovietled 
invasion of czechoslovakia 
the balkan nation then broke with china in 1978 and established 
a course fiercely independent of both military blocs it prided 
itself on being selfreliant and claimed to be the only country 
practicing true communism 
albania also has no relations with the united states 
it has vowed to resist the democratic reforms sweeping eastern 
europe and still reveres the late soviet leader josef stalin even 
more important is communist albanias founding father enver hoxha 
who died in 1985 
but in recent weeks albanian citizens demanding change forced 
their way into foreign embassies in tirana and were allowed to 
leave the country 
