proposal in budget negotiations to raise federal revenues by 
limiting the deduction for state income taxes a proposal 
governors say encroaches on state tax bases 
to eliminate this deduction would result in a double tax on 
our citizens said the letter 
it was being pushed by massachusetts gov michael dukakis whom 
bush defeated in the 1988 presidential election and maryland gov 
william donald schaefer 
the notion of putting the burden on the states again for 
washingtons inability to deal with its fiscal problems is just 
