slaying so far 22 people have been charged in this country and 
more than 20 convicted in mexico 
the trial is the second prosecution in the case in los angeles 
in 1988 a drug trafficker and a former mexican policeman were 
convicted in federal court of multiple charges including murder 
in the camarena case and another drug trafficker was found guilty 
of aiding and abetting the murders 
camarena 31 was kidnapped off a guadalajara street according 
to testimony at both trials he was taken to caros house where he 
was tortured and interrogated before being slain along with his 
pilot their bodies were found a month later on a ranch 65 miles 
from gaudalajara 
the murders were said to be in retribution for dea drug seizures 
which cost the drug barons 5 billion in profits 
judge edward rafeedie set bernabes sentencing for sept 24 and 
ordered lawyers to refrain from comment on the case until all 
verdicts have been returned 
the two remaining defendants are ruben zuno arce a guadalajara 
businessman and brotherinlaw of former mexican president luis 
