saturday and this is monday morning and were still talking about 
what equipment to put where and where we are going to get the 
equipment from 
wynne and mauro plan on tuesday to present coast guard officials 
with a plan to use oileating microbes on the spill the state 
tried the microbes on the mega borg spill and said theyd reduced 
the oil in the test area 
these tidal wetlands are very sensitive wynne said if oil 
gets in there it might be more difficult to clean up with 
conventional methods he said use of skimmers or other mechanical 
devices could endanger shallow marshlands and sensitive estuaries 
