<TEXT>
dont be surprised if jane curtin loses 
control occasionally in her role as a divorced mother in the nbc 
fall show working it out 
in the pilot for the new saturday night comedy which costars 
stephen collins she had wanted to show that she was not reprising 
her emmywinning role from kate amp allie 
it was important for me to show that she was very different 
from allie that she had everything under control she says 
but the pilot seemed to be too onenote she was too much in 
control 
in the future well show that beneath that shes lava liquid 
rock youll see her control crumble from time to time it makes 
her more human 
curtin stars as sarah marshall the divorced mother of a 
9yearold she isnt looking for any new relationships until she 
meets david stuart collins at a cooking class stuart is a 
photographer who has finally gotten his own daughter out of the 
house and isnt interested in anyone with a young child of course 
that all goes out the window as they start working it out 
curtins last regular character allie had considerably less 
control of her life curtin costarred with susan saint james for 
five years in kate amp allie allie was a homebody with two 
children who preferred standing over a hot stove to dating she 
was a great cook who could never get a grip on things although in 
the final season in 1988 she got married 
this fall nbc has all halfhour comedies on saturday including 
three new shows parenthood based on the hit movie begins the 
night followed by working it out the returning hit shows 
the golden girls empty nest and carol amp co and 
another new comedy american dreamer 
cbs counters with a mixture of comedy drama and news while abc 
has three onehour dramas including twin peaks at 10 pm 
working it out like kate amp allie and saturday night 
live is produced in new york other than a few movies curtin 
has worked mostly in new york to be near her husband and daughter 
she talked about the show during a brief visit to los angeles to 
promote the series 
i was looking for a project and was in contact with bill 
persky she said persky had been the executive producer of 
kate amp allie he was doing a film and i thought i should go 
off and do something different then at the last minute we felt we 
should do something together he sent me a pilot script he had 
written and many lunches and calories later we decided to go with 
it billy didnt write it for me and originally he only wanted me 
to look at it but i liked it and wanted to work with billy again 
if you have the same rhythm as billy and i do its the best 
condition for working you just fly through hes very open to 
suggestions you never feel inhibited 
prior to working it out curtin had spent some time 
developing a comedy news show with buck henry and others 
it would have been like one of those pontifical roundtable 
shows she says we kept trying to get something on as a 
segment of the connie chung show it didnt work out that was last 
november and every time we did anything the events changed 
curtin had been an anchor on weekend update on saturday night 
live after the departure of chevy chase 
she had been with the proposition an improvisational theater 
group before joining saturday night live in 1975 as an 
original member of the not ready for prime time players 
the proposition would occasionally perform on television 
she says usually after each performance wed never be invited 
back because wed manage to offend them in some way 
curtin reportedly said on leaving saturday night live that 
she would never return asked if she would ever return for a guest 
role she flashes a grin and replies if it were on earlier say 
9 or 930 pm 
she left the latenight show in 1980 and went on to continued 
television stardom she won two emmys for her role in kate amp 
allie she did not achieve the feature film success of such snl 
alums as chase dan aykroyd and john belushi and later billy 
crystal bill murray and eddie murphy 
one of her first movies was how to beat the high cost of 
living which went nowhere the movie however did team her for 
the first time with susan saint james which may have figured in 
their pairing later in kate amp allie garrett morris also from 
saturday night live was also in the movie as was dabney 
coleman her costar in the tv movie maybe baby she starred 
with tom selleck in divorce wars 
this past season she played alice mcgoff a widow with seven 
children who fought school integration in boston in the miniseries 
common ground that was the first bluecollar role for curtin 
and a change of pace 
its so hard to hide good breeding she jokes its a 
curse 
</TEXT>
