inherent weakness in the dollar 
many dealers thought that with the end of the month there 
would be an increased demand for dollars but that seems not to 
have materialized she said 
nevertheless she predicted the dollar would not fall much 
further bottoming out somewhere around 14740 yen 
on the stock market the closely watched nikkei stock average of 
225 selected issues rose 43664 points or 143 percent to 
3087959 points 30 minutes after trading began 
the nikkei average has lost 217603 points or 658 percent 
since july 19 
the price of the benchmark no 119 10year japanese government 
bond also reversed its direction tuesday morning rising to 8523 
points from 8514 points at the monday close yields fell to 7585 
percent from 7605 percent 
