<DOCNO> AP900730-0226 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
varity corp one of the worlds largest farm 
equipment makers plans to ask shareholders for permission to move 
its headquarters to buffalo ny company officials said monday 
varity is already a us company with a canadian address 
because over 80 percent of its shareholders live in the united 
states said victor rice the companys chairman and chief 
executive officer 
most of varitys north american employees work in us plants 
and usbased customers will account for some 50 percent of 1990 
revenues displacing europe as the companys biggest market rice 
said 
he said varity as a us company would rank among the 
countrys top 130 publicly traded enterprises 
varity is considering a headquarters move to buffalo to make its 
stock more widely available to us investors and to relieve them 
of the canadian governments 15 percent withholding tax on 
dividends company officials say 
but canadian officials have said their government will sue if 
necessary to block the move 
the move would violate a pledge varity then known as 
masseyferguson made in 1986 in return for a 1691 million 
government bailout according to officials of the ontario 
development corp a quasipublic agency that funnels government 
loans to businesses 
the officials say varity agreed to maintain or create 1500 jobs 
in canada by 1993 and also keep its headquarters there 
varity recently purchased a mansion in buffalo and won an 115 
million package of tax exemptions from the erie county industrial 
development agency those actions prompted public warnings from 
canadian officials that varity would face a court fight if it moved 
its headquarters 
</TEXT>
